Horseman Capital Management LTD Has Increased Nvidia (NVDA) Position by $2.44 Million; Valuation Rose, Amphenol (APH) Shareholder Holland Capital Management Increased Holding


					

						July 25, 2017 - By Max Morgan

Holland Capital Management Llc increased its stake in Amphenol (APH) by 19.9% based on its latest 2016Q4 regulatory filing with the SEC. Holland Capital Management Llc bought 5,593 shares as the company’s stock rose 4.95% with the market. The institutional investor held 33,694 shares of the electrical products company at the end of 2016Q4, valued at $2.26 million, up from 28,101 at the end of the previous reported quarter. Holland Capital Management Llc who had been investing in Amphenol for a number of months, seems to be bullish on the $23.14 billion market cap company. It closed at $75.64 lastly. It is down 31.78% since July 25, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 15.08% the S&P500.
John Horseman increased its stake in Nvidia Corp (NVDA) by 104.55% based on its latest 2016Q4 regulatory filing with the SEC. Horseman Capital Management Ltd bought 23,000 shares as the company’s stock rose 26.83% with the market. The hedge fund run by John Horseman held 45,000 shares of the semiconductors company at the end of 2016Q4, valued at $4.80 million, up from 22,000 at the end of the previous reported quarter. Horseman Capital Management Ltd who had been investing in Nvidia Corp for a number of months, seems to be bullish on the $97.71B market cap company. The stock declined 0.88% or $1.46 reaching $164.69 on the news. About 47,480 shares traded. NVIDIA Corporation (NASDAQ:NVDA) has risen 212.28% since July 25, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 195.58% the S&P500.







More notable recent NVIDIA Corporation (NASDAQ:NVDA) news were published by: Fool.com which released: “5 Reasons NVIDIA Corporation Stock Could Fall” on July 01, 2017, also Fool.com with their article: “Digging Into This Questionable NVIDIA Corporation Rumor” published on June 26, 2017, Investorplace.com published: “Nvidia Corporation (NVDA) Stock Is No Longer the Best Play on AI” on July 24, 2017. More interesting news about NVIDIA Corporation (NASDAQ:NVDA) were released by: Fool.com and their article: “Forget NVIDIA Corporation: These 4 Stocks Doubled Last Year” published on July 08, 2017 as well as Investorplace.com‘s news article titled: “Nvidia Corporation (NVDA) Stock Will Hit New All-Time Highs Soon” with publication date: July 21, 2017.
