(NASDAQ:AMZN) previously announced its fiscal periodic earnings information on Early Thur, Apr 27th. Cowen and Company reaffirmed an "outperform" rating and issued a $1,050.00 price target on shares of Amazon.com in a research report on Monday, April 10th. Amazon.com also was the recipient of some unusual options trading activity on Thursday. From the opening price, the stock has seen a change of -1.96% recently clocking in with a price of $1049.05. It fall, as 126 investors sold AMZN shares while 478 reduced holdings. The stock was unloaded at a price range of of $940.45, amounting $630,101.50. Greenleaf Trust now owns 1,129 shares of the e-commerce giant's stock worth $1,001,000 after buying an additional 54 shares during the last quarter. WealthTrust Arizona LLC now owns 114 shares of the e-commerce giant's stock worth $110,000 after buying an additional 3 shares during the last quarter.Over the last 5 years, Amazon.com, Inc. has averaged a 29.00% YoY EPS growth rate and a 23.10% revenue growth rate.According to Balance Sheet of AMZN, Total cash on most recent quarter is 21.53 Billion.
