Horseman Capital Management LTD Lifted Burlington Stores (BURL) Position, Invesco Municipal Opportunity Trust (VMO)’s Sentiment Is 1.08


					

						July 25, 2017 - By Adrian Erickson

Invesco Van Kampen Municipal Opportunity Trust , formerly Invesco Municipal Opportunity Trust is a diversified, closed-end management investment trust. The company has market cap of $834.62 million. The Trust’s investment objective is to provide common shareholders with a high level of current income exempt from federal income tax, consistent with preservation of capital. It currently has negative earnings. Under normal market conditions, the Trust will invest approximately 80% of its net assets in municipal securities rated investment grade at the time of investment.
Horseman Capital Management Ltd increased Burlington Stores Inc (BURL) stake by 0.78% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Horseman Capital Management Ltd acquired 3,900 shares as Burlington Stores Inc (BURL)’s stock rose 10.27%. The Horseman Capital Management Ltd holds 503,900 shares with $42.71M value, up from 500,000 last quarter. Burlington Stores Inc now has $5.80B valuation. The stock decreased 1.02% or $0.87 during the last trading session, reaching $84.82. About shares traded. Burlington Stores Inc (NYSE:BURL) has risen 77.68% since July 25, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 60.98% the S&P500.






Among 14 analysts covering Burlington Stores (NYSE:BURL), 12 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 2 Hold. Therefore 86% are positive. Burlington Stores had 33 analyst reports since October 7, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The rating was maintained by BMO Capital Markets on Wednesday, April 19 with “Buy”. Citigroup initiated the shares of BURL in report on Wednesday, October 7 with “Buy” rating. Wolfe Research initiated the stock with “Outperform” rating in Friday, April 28 report. Goldman Sachs upgraded the stock to “Buy” rating in Thursday, January 21 report. The rating was maintained by Citigroup with “Neutral” on Friday, August 26. The firm has “Outperform” rating by RBC Capital Markets given on Friday, May 27. RBC Capital Markets initiated Burlington Stores Inc (NYSE:BURL) rating on Friday, November 6. RBC Capital Markets has “Outperform” rating and $58 target. On Tuesday, May 30 the stock rating was maintained by Cowen & Co with “Buy”. RBC Capital Markets maintained it with “Outperform” rating and $97 target in Friday, March 3 report. The firm earned “Outperform” rating on Friday, June 23 by Cowen & Co.
Investors sentiment increased to 1.09 in 2016 Q4. Its up 0.20, from 0.89 in 2016Q3. It increased, as 31 investors sold BURL shares while 104 reduced holdings. 56 funds opened positions while 91 raised stakes. 71.03 million shares or 1.25% less from 71.93 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. First Personal Finance stated it has 361 shares or 0.01% of all its holdings. Nuveen Asset Mngmt Limited Co reported 0.03% stake. Waddell And Reed Incorporated, Kansas-based fund reported 492,620 shares. Moreover, Capstone Investment Advisors Ltd Llc has 0.04% invested in Burlington Stores Inc (NYSE:BURL) for 13,990 shares. The Ontario – Canada-based Breton Hill Capital Ltd has invested 0.06% in Burlington Stores Inc (NYSE:BURL). Eagle Asset Management owns 1.96M shares or 1.09% of their US portfolio. Castleark Management Ltd holds 133,963 shares or 0.36% of its portfolio. The New Jersey-based Bessemer Grp Inc Inc has invested 0% in Burlington Stores Inc (NYSE:BURL). M&T Fincl Bank reported 2,546 shares or 0% of all its holdings. Ipg Advisors Ltd Limited Liability Company holds 14,800 shares. 934,611 were reported by Samlyn Capital Limited Co. 28,792 are held by Legal General Grp Public Limited Liability Company. Massmutual Fsb Adv has 30 shares for 0% of their portfolio. 811,036 are held by Deutsche Bancshares Ag. 438,861 are owned by Tiaa Cref Mngmt Limited Liability Company.
Since February 1, 2017, it had 0 insider purchases, and 18 insider sales for $21.33 million activity. Another trade for 7,335 shares valued at $690,955 was made by Crimmins John on Wednesday, March 8. On Wednesday, February 1 MAGRINI JOYCE MANNING sold $289,160 worth of Burlington Stores Inc (NYSE:BURL) or 3,500 shares. $1.86M worth of Burlington Stores Inc (NYSE:BURL) shares were sold by Kingsbury Thomas. $1.26M worth of Burlington Stores Inc (NYSE:BURL) shares were sold by Hand Fred. Another trade for 6,959 shares valued at $654,466 was sold by Sullivan Paul. Another trade for 10,000 shares valued at $967,996 was made by Katz Marc on Tuesday, May 30.
Summit Financial Wealth Advisors Llc holds 0.65% of its portfolio in Invesco Van Kampen Municpl Opprtnty Trst for 115,225 shares. Fca Corp Tx owns 86,097 shares or 0.55% of their US portfolio. Moreover, Jfs Wealth Advisors Llc has 0.49% invested in the company for 142,076 shares. The Texas-based Fiduciary Financial Services Of The Southwest Inc Tx has invested 0.24% in the stock. Tradewinds Capital Management Llc, a Washington-based fund reported 21,000 shares.
The stock decreased 0.53% or $0.07 on July 24, reaching $13.11. About shares traded. Invesco Van Kampen Municpl Opprtnty Trst (VMO) has declined 7.13% since July 25, 2016 and is downtrending. It has underperformed by 23.83% the S&P500.



