Horseman Capital Management LTD Lowered Sociedad Quimica Y Minera De Chile Sa (SQM) Stake By $1.96 Million; Zebra Technologies (ZBRA)’s Sentiment Is 0.85


					

						July 24, 2017 - By Clifton Ray

Horseman Capital Management Ltd decreased Sociedad Quimica Y Minera De Chile Sa (SQM) stake by 44.47% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Horseman Capital Management Ltd sold 69,900 shares as Sociedad Quimica Y Minera De Chile Sa (SQM)’s stock rose 11.91%. The Horseman Capital Management Ltd holds 87,300 shares with $2.50 million value, down from 157,200 last quarter. Sociedad Quimica Y Minera De Chile Sa now has $9.97 billion valuation. The stock increased 0.65% or $0.25 on July 21, reaching $38.63. About shares traded. Sociedad Quimica y Minera de Chile (ADR) (NYSE:SQM) has risen 69.80% since July 24, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 53.10% the S&P500.






Zebra Technologies Corporation designs, makes and sells a range of automatic identification and data capture products. The company has market cap of $5.15 billion. The Company’s AIDC products include mobile computers, barcode scanners, radio frequency identification (RFID) readers, wireless local area network (WLAN) products, specialty printers for barcode labeling and personal identification, real-time location systems (RTLS), related accessories and supplies, such as self-adhesive labels and other consumables, and utilities and application software. It currently has negative earnings. The Firm operates through two divisions: Enterprise, which comprises its mobile computing, data capture, RFID and WLAN products, and services, and Legacy Zebra, which comprises barcode and card printing, location solutions, supplies and services.
Analysts await Zebra Technologies Corp. (NASDAQ:ZBRA) to report earnings on August, 8. They expect $1.35 EPS, up 4.65% or $0.06 from last year’s $1.29 per share. ZBRA’s profit will be $70.35 million for 18.30 P/E if the $1.35 EPS becomes a reality. After $1.27 actual EPS reported by Zebra Technologies Corp. for the previous quarter, Wall Street now forecasts 6.30% EPS growth. 
Makaira Partners Llc holds 14.7% of its portfolio in Zebra Technologies Corp. for 1.18 million shares. Goodnow Investment Group Llc owns 483,569 shares or 9.24% of their US portfolio. Moreover, New South Capital Management Inc has 5.2% invested in the company for 2.54 million shares. The Pennsylvania-based Snow Capital Management Lp has invested 2.55% in the stock. Ariel Investments Llc, a Illinois-based fund reported 2.14 million shares.
The stock decreased 1.17% or $1.17 on July 21, reaching $98.83. About shares traded. Zebra Technologies Corp. (ZBRA) has risen 101.68% since July 24, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 84.98% the S&P500.
Since January 1, 0001, it had 0 buys, and 7 insider sales for $7.50 million activity. 



